  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default, an action with a duration applies its changes linearly over the duration you specify. However, you can adjust the timing of actions."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Add or Change Properties to Adjust the Timing of an Action",
          "anchor": "3109027"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "These options are available: "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Use an actionâ€™s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skaction/1417807-timingmode"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property to choose a nonlinear timing mode for an animation. For example, you can have the action start quickly and then slow down over the remainder of the run (see "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skactiontimingmode"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ")."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Create a custom timing function if you want finer control over an action's timing. See "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skaction/1417666-timingfunction"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Speed up or slow down an animation from its default timing using an actionâ€™s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "speed"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property, which changes the rate at which an animation plays. A "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "speed"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " value of "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "1.0"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " is the normal rate, but if you set an actionâ€™s speed property to, for example, "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "2.0"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", SpriteKit plays the animation twice as fast. To pause the action, set the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "speed"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " to "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "0"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ". If you adjust the speed of an action that contains other actions (such as a group, sequence, or repeating action), the rate is applied to the actions contained within. The contained actions are also affected by their own speed property."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A nodeâ€™s speed property has the same effect as the actionâ€™s speed property, but the rate is applied to all actions processed by the node or any of its descendants in the scene tree."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Because there are multiple rates involved in an animation's speed, SpriteKit finds all the rates that apply to the action and multiplies them to determine the final rate."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Cancel Actions that Should Be Stopped",
          "anchor": "2984813"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To cancel actions that a node is running, call its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/1483030-removeallactions"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method. All actions are removed from the node immediately. If a removed action had a duration, any changes it already made to the node remain intact, but further changes are not executed."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
